class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span>                              <span class=\"o\">|</span>  <span class=\"mi\">5</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">STRING</span>  <span class=\"o\">|</span>     <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>       <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"keks\"</span>                         <span class=\"o\">|</span>  <span class=\"mi\">6</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">ARRAY</span>   <span class=\"o\">|</span>     <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>       <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">\"eins\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"zwei\"</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>               <span class=\"o\">|</span>  <span class=\"mi\">7</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">OBJECT</span>  <span class=\"o\">|</span>     <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>       <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"err\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">\"eins\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"one\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"zwei\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"two\"</span><span class=\"err\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>  <span class=\"mi\">8</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">---------+-------+---------+--------------------------------+----+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">8</span> <span class=\"k\">rows</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">insert</span> <span class=\"k\">into</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">values</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'[\"incomplete\", \"array\", \"closing bracket\"'</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ERROR</span> <span class=\"mi\">3140</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">22032</span><span class=\"p\">):</span> <span class=\"n\">Invalid</span> <span class=\"n\">JSON</span> <span class=\"nb\">text</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"Missing a comma or ']' after an array element.\"</span> <span class=\"k\">at</span> <span class=\"k\">position</span> <span class=\"mi\">41</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"n\">value</span> <span class=\"k\">for</span> <span class=\"k\">column</span> <span class=\"s1\">'t.j'</span><span class=\"p\">.</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>We learn several things from this experiment:</p> \n<ul> \n <li>Literal JSON values are always simple strings. \n  <ul> \n   <li>The character set in JSON objects is <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">utf8mb4</code>, the collation is <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">utf8mb4_bin</code>.</li> \n   <li>Because the collation is a <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">_bin</code> collation, comparison is case sensitive. Charset and collation are fixed and cannot be changed without casting to a non-JSON type.</li> \n   <li>We enclose them in single quotes, leveraging the fact that MySQL allows both single and double quotes as string terminators. This saves us a lot of quoting.</li> \n   <li>JSON null is written as the string <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">'null'</code>.</li> \n   <li>JSON true is written as the string <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">'true'</code>.</li> \n   <li>JSON false is written as the string <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">'false'</code>.</li> \n  </ul> </li> \n <li>We allowed NULL values in our JSON column definition by not providing a <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">NOT NULL</code> clause. SQL <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">NULL</code> is different from JSON <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">'null'</code>, but is cast to this.</li> \n <li>We can use the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_TYPE()</code> function to check the JSON type inside the JSON column.</li> \n <li>The JSON is parsed, and checked for validity. The <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_VALID()</code> function does the checking. \n  <ul> \n   <li>It also exposes the difference between SQL <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">NULL</code> and JSON <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">'null'</code>. So does the SQL <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">ISNULL()</code> function (or the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">IS NULL</code> comparison operator).</li> \n  </ul> </li> \n</ul> \n<h2>Creating JSON values</h2> \n<p>We can see JSON literal notation already from the previous example. There are also two utility functions to construct JSON array and object structures from SQL scalars. They are <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_ARRAY()</code> and <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_OBJECT()</code>. Note the handling of SQL <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">NULL</code> values.</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">json_array</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"k\">NULL</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">ary</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">json_object</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">\"eins\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"one\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"null\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"k\">NULL</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"zwei\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"two\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">obj</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------------+----------------------------------------------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">ary</span>          <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">obj</span>                                          <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------------+----------------------------------------------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"k\">null</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"err\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">\"eins\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"one\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"null\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"k\">null</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"zwei\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"two\"</span><span class=\"err\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------------+----------------------------------------------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">01</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>We can use <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_MERGE_PRESERVE()</code> and <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_MERGE_PATCH()</code> to incrementally build complicated structures. <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_MERGE_PRESERVE()</code> replaces <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_MERGE()</code>, which is deprecaged and should no longer be used.</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">json_merge_preserve</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'[3, 4, 5]'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'[1, 2, 3]'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">preserve</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">json_merge_patch</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'[1, 2, 3]'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'[3, 4, 5]'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">patch</span><span class=\"err\">\\</span><span class=\"k\">G</span>\n<span class=\"k\">preserve</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n   <span class=\"n\">patch</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">json_merge_preserve</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'{\"eins\": \"one\", \"zwei\": \"two\"}'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'{\"zwei\": \"two\", \"drei\": \"three\"}'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">preserve</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">json_merge_patch</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'{\"eins\": \"one\", \"zwei\": \"two\"}'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'{\"zwei\": \"two\", \"drei\": \"three\"}'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">patch</span><span class=\"err\">\\</span><span class=\"k\">G</span>\n<span class=\"k\">preserve</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"err\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">\"drei\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"three\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"eins\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"one\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"zwei\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">\"two\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"two\"</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"err\">}</span>\n   <span class=\"n\">patch</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"err\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">\"drei\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"three\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"eins\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"one\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"zwei\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"two\"</span><span class=\"err\">}</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>Quotes and quoting can be a bit painful, and even confusing. Let’s put the string <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">A so-called \"string\".</code> into a JSON string, inside an SQL statement. To turn this text into a JSON string we need to put double quotes around it, quoting our internal double quotes with backslashes. To produce a backslash literal, we need to write a double backslash.</p> \n<p>The result:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">insert</span> <span class=\"k\">into</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">values</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'\"A so-called </span><span class=\"se\">\\\\</span><span class=\"s1\">\"string</span><span class=\"se\">\\\\</span><span class=\"s1\">\".\"'</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Query</span> <span class=\"n\">OK</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"n\">affected</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">02</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">last_insert_id</span><span class=\"p\">()</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span><span class=\"err\">\\</span><span class=\"k\">G</span>\n<span class=\"n\">id</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">9</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>We can get this back as <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">j</code>, or use JSON extractors (<code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_EXTRACT()</code>, or <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">-&gt;</code>). The current document is <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">$</code>, so:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"s1\">'$'</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">jj</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"s1\">'$'</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">jj_unquoted</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"k\">where</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">9</span><span class=\"err\">\\</span><span class=\"k\">G</span>\n          <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"A so-called </span><span class=\"se\">\\\"</span><span class=\"nv\">string</span><span class=\"se\">\\\"</span><span class=\"nv\">.\"</span>\n         <span class=\"n\">jj</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"A so-called </span><span class=\"se\">\\\"</span><span class=\"nv\">string</span><span class=\"se\">\\\"</span><span class=\"nv\">.\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">jj_unquoted</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">A</span> <span class=\"n\">so</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">called</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"string\"</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>This brings us to component access:</p> \n<h2>JSON component access</h2> \n<p>Using the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_EXTRACT()</code> function and JSON path syntax, we can access fields in the JSON and select for them, as foreshadowed above.</p> \n<p>We get the following selectors:</p> \n<ul> \n <li> <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">$</code>, the current JSON document.</li> \n <li> <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">.key</code>, select the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">key</code> from the current object. Use <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">.\"key with space\"</code> when necessary.</li> \n <li> <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">[N]</code> selects the element <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">N</code> from a JSON array, starting to count at 0. \n  <ul> \n   <li> <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">.\"equipment-ids\"[1]</code> is interesting, because we need to quote <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">\"equipment-ids\"</code> due to the dash in the key name. We must not put the array index into the quotes, though, or it won’t work.</li> \n   <li>For an array slice, the syntax is <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">[M to N]</code> for the slice from <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">N</code> to <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">M</code> inclusive.</li> \n   <li>For arrays, the keyword <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">last</code> is the rightmost element in the array.</li> \n  </ul> </li> \n <li>There are wildcards: \n  <ul> \n   <li> <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">.*</code> are all values of a JSON object, as an array.</li> \n   <li> <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">[*]</code> are all the values of a JSON array, as an array.</li> \n   <li> <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">**</code> are all paths that lead to a suffix.</li> \n  </ul> </li> \n</ul> \n<p>So, put into practice:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">insert</span> <span class=\"k\">into</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">id</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">values</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'{\"id\": 10, \"login\": \"kris\", \"fullname\": \"Kristian </span><span class=\"se\">\\\\</span><span class=\"s1\">\"Isotopp</span><span class=\"se\">\\\\</span><span class=\"s1\">\" Köhntopp\", \"equipment-ids\": [10, 11, 12], \"borrowed\":{ \"equipment-ids\": [1,2,3]}}'</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Query</span> <span class=\"n\">OK</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"n\">affected</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">01</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">json_extract</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'$.fullname'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">f1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">json_value</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'$.fullname'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">f2</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"k\">where</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"err\">\\</span><span class=\"k\">G</span>\n<span class=\"n\">f1</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"Kristian </span><span class=\"se\">\\\"</span><span class=\"nv\">Isotopp</span><span class=\"se\">\\\"</span><span class=\"nv\"> Köhntopp\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">f2</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Kristian</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"Isotopp\"</span> <span class=\"n\">K</span><span class=\"err\">ö</span><span class=\"n\">hntopp</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">json_extract</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'$.\"equipment-ids\"[1]'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">jj</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"k\">where</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"err\">\\</span><span class=\"k\">G</span>\n<span class=\"n\">jj</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">11</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">json_extract</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'$.\"equipment-ids\"[1 to 2]'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">jj</span> <span <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_EXTRACT(colname, selector)</code> function:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">03</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>We can ask for the payment status of all our users already, using the syntax from above:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"c1\">--------+-------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"kris\"</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span>  <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">--------+-------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"k\">rows</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>We cannot SQL <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">SELECT</code> all users that have paid, yet:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span>  <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">-------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span>  <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">false</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">-------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"k\">rows</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"n\">warning</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">Warning</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Code</span> <span class=\"mi\">3986</span><span class=\"p\">):</span> <span class=\"n\">Evaluating</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"n\">JSON</span> <span class=\"n\">value</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">SQL</span> <span class=\"nb\">boolean</span> <span class=\"n\">context</span> <span class=\"n\">does</span> <span class=\"n\">an</span> <span class=\"k\">implicit</span> <span class=\"n\">comparison</span> <span class=\"n\">against</span> <span class=\"n\">JSON</span> <span class=\"nb\">integer</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">;</span> <span class=\"n\">if</span> <span class=\"n\">this</span> <span class=\"k\">is</span> <span class=\"k\">not</span> <span class=\"n\">what</span> <span class=\"n\">you</span> <span class=\"n\">want</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">consider</span> <span class=\"n\">converting</span> <span class=\"n\">JSON</span> <span class=\"k\">to</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"k\">SQL</span> <span class=\"nb\">numeric</span> <span class=\"k\">type</span> <span class=\"k\">with</span> <span class=\"n\">JSON_VALUE</span> <span class=\"n\">RETURNING</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"k\">where</span> <span class=\"n\">json_value</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'$.paid'</span> <span class=\"n\">returning</span> <span class=\"nb\">signed</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span>   <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"kris\"</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>The function <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/json-search-functions.html#function_json-value\"><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_VALUE()</code></a> provides a type cast from JSON to SQL, making extracted JSON values available to SQL comparisons and conditions. Follow the link and look it up. There is no <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">INTEGER</code>, you have to be more specific, <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">SIGNED</code> or <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">UNSIGNED</code>, the types match the ones used in <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">CAST()</code>. There are also <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">ON EMPTY</code> and <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">ON ERROR</code> clauses.</p> \n<p>Using <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_VALUE()</code> we can do the work of <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_EXTRACT()</code>, <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_UNQUOTE()</code> and <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">CAST()</code> in one go, and have control about handling of non-existent paths (<code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">ON EMPTY</code>) and conversion errors (<code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">ON ERROR</code>).</p> \n<p>We could have used cast as well:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>   <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>   <span class=\"k\">cast</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"nb\">signed</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">casted</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>   <span class=\"n\">json_value</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"n\">returning</span> <span class=\"nb\">signed</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">valued</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+-------+--------+--------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span>   <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span>  <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">casted</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">valued</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+-------+--------+--------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"kris\"</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span>  <span class=\"o\">|</span>      <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>      <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"sven\"</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">false</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>      <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>      <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+-------+--------+--------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"k\">rows</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span>   <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span>\n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">where</span> <span class=\"k\">cast</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"nb\">signed</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span>   <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"kris\"</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">where</span> <span class=\"n\">json_value</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"n\">returning</span> <span class=\"nb\">signed</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span>   <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"kris\"</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>Note that I left out the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_UNQUOTE()</code> in the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">CAST()</code> example, because I converted JSON <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">BOOLEAN</code> types to SQL <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">SIGNED</code> types, so no quoted strings needed handling. <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_VALUE(col, selector RETURNING type)</code> is actually <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">CAST(JSON_UNQUOTE(JSON_EXTRACT(col, selector)) AS type)</code>.</p> \n<h2>Updating JSON values</h2> \n<p>Reusing the example above, we can try to update the payment status of a user using the <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/json-modification-functions.html#function_json-set\"><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_SET()</code></a> function. Doing this, we need to be careful.</p> \n<p>First, let’s check if we can isolate the row we want to see elegantly:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>  \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">json_type</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+-------+---------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span>   <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span>  <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span>    <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+-------+---------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"kris\"</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span>  <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nb\">BOOLEAN</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"sven\"</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">false</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nb\">BOOLEAN</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+-------+---------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"k\">rows</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">where</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"kris\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span>   <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"kris\"</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">true</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.paid\"</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">where</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"nv\">\"$.user\"</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"nv\">\"KRIS\"</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Empty</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>We notice: while this works, it is working with JSON character sets, so it is <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">utf8mb4</code> with a collation of <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">utf8mb4_bin</code>, hence case sensitive comparison.</p> \n<p>Using <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_SET()</code> we update the <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">$.paid</code> field of that user to <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">false</code>, and run into the next problem:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">update</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span> \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">json_set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span <span class=\"nv\">\"sven\"</span><span class=\"err\">}</span>   <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span \n<span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+---------+---------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">user</span>   <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span>    <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">paid</span>    <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">--------+---------+---------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>That is not what we want. But did we not insert values <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">\"false\"</code> and <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">\"true\"</code> into JSON fields earlier and got booleans?</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">insert</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>Well, yes, but…</p> \n<p>Functions in MySQL expect types, and convert to these types. <code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_SET()</code> expects JSON, so we do it like this:</p> \n<figure class=\"highlight\">\n <pre><code class=\"language-sql\" data-lang=\"sql\"><span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"n\">affected</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span <span class=\"n\">Changed</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span>  <span class=\"n\">Warnings</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">mysql</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"k\">select</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">json_type</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"k\">type</span> <span class=\"k\">from</span> <span class=\"c1\">----+-------+---------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">id</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">j</span>     <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">type</span>    <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">----+-------+---------+</span>\n<span class=\"o\">|</span>  <span class=\"mi\">3</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"k\">false</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span> <span class=\"nb\">BOOLEAN</span> <span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"c1\">----+-------+---------+</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">1</span> <span class=\"k\">row</span> <span class=\"k\">in</span> <span class=\"k\">set</span> <span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">00</span> <span class=\"n\">sec</span><span class=\"p\">)</span></code></pre>\n</figure>\n<p>There is <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/json-modification-functions.html#function_json-remove\"><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_REMOVE()</code></a>, “Removes data from a JSON document”. There are also <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/json-modification-functions.html#function_json-set\"><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_SET()</code></a>, and friends:</p> \n<ul> \n <li> <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/json-modification-functions.html#function_json-set\"><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_SET()</code></a> replaces existing values and adds nonexisting values.</li> \n <li> <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/json-modification-functions.html#function_json-insert\"><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_INSERT()</code></a> inserts values without replacing existing values.</li> \n <li> <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/json-modification-functions.html#function_json-replace\"><code class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">JSON_REPLACE()</code></a> replaces only existing values.</li> \n</ul>","descriptionType":"html","publishedDate":"Thu, 03 Sep 2020 20:57:10 Introduced in MySQL 8.0.21?","link":"https://mysqlsolutionsarchitect.blogspot.com/2020/09/how-to-take-mysql-enterprise-edition.html","description":"<h2>&nbsp;Using Instance Dump and Schema Dump features introduced in MySQL 8.0.21 Version.</h2> \n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In this Blog I will cover below topic:-<p></p></p> \n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">\n <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>1.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n <!--[endif]-->What is Instance Dump/Schema Dump features all about?<p></p></p> \n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>2.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n <!--[endif]-->What are advantage?<p></p></p> \n<p Benchmarks?<p></p></p> \n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">\n <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>5.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n <!--[endif]-->Conclusion<p></p></p> \n<h3>What is Instance Dump/Schema Dump features all about?</h3> \n<h1><p></p></h1> \n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"MsoTableGrid\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr> \n   <td valign=\"top\" width=\"471\"> <p class=\"MsoNormal\">MySQL Instance Dump is another logical back up option where backup can be processed in multi-threaded with file compress which will help users to improve <b>performance </b>of overall backup process and also save disk space.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\">This features is introduced in MySQL 8.0.21, which means to utilize these features you must use client <b>MySQL SHELL 8.0.21 version.<p></p></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>To perform instance Dump there is utility called <span>util.dumpInstance(outputUrl[, options])</span></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\">In short<b><span>, util.dumpInstance(): </span></b><span>dump an entire database instance, including users.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\">MySQL Schema Dump is another customize options where users can perform back up of choice, let’s say if you wanted to take one single/multiple databases or else particular table <span>&nbsp;</span>then we use utility called <b>“Schema Dump Utility” </b><b><span><span>à</span></span> <span>util.dumpSchemas</span></b></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\">In short, <b><span>util.dumpSchemas():</span></b><span> </span><span>dump a set of schemas.</span></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\">The dumps created by MySQL Shell's instance dump utility and schema dump utility comprise DDL files specifying the schema structure, and tab-separated .tsv files containing the data.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoNormal\">By default, the dump utilities chunk table data into multiple data files and compress the files.<p></p></p> </td> \n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table> \n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><p>&nbsp;</p></p> \n<h3>What are things can be done with Instance Dump</h3> \n<h1><p></p></h1> \n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"MsoTableGrid\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr> \n   <td valign=\"top\" width=\"471\"> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>1.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->Backing to Oracle Cloud Infrastructure Object Storage.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>2.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->Backing Up to local machine directory.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>3.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->Helpful in provisioning new Instance in on-premises as well as on Cloud.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\"><p>&nbsp;</p></p> </td> \n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table> \n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><p>&nbsp;</p></p> \n<h3>Requirements apply to dumps using the instance dump utility and schema dump utility:</h3> \n<h1><p></p></h1> \n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><p>&nbsp;-</p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span><span>MySQL 5.7 or later is required for both the source MySQL instance and the destination MySQL instance.</span></p> \n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\"><p></p></p> \n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span>Object names in the instance or schema must be in the latin1 or utf8 characterset.<p></p></p> \n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n <!--[endif]-->Data consistency is guaranteed only for tables that use the InnoDB storage engine.<p></p></p> \n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">\n <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n <!--[endif]-->The upload method used to transfer files to an Oracle Cloud Infrastructure Object Storage bucket has a file size limit of 1.2 TiB.<p></p></p> \n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">More info: - <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql-shell/8.0/en/mysql-shell-utilities-dump-instance-schema.html\">https://dev.mysql.com/doc/mysql-shell/8.0/en/mysql-shell-utilities-dump-instance-schema.html</a><p></p></p> \n<h3>What is Advantage of using Instance Dump?</h3> \n<h1><p></p></h1> \n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"MsoTableGrid\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr> \n   <td valign=\"top\" width=\"471\"> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->It is parallel dumping with multiple threads.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->Automatic file compression – zstd algorithm. The alternatives are to use gzip compression (gzip) or no compression (none).<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->Improved Performance than mysqldump.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->Flexibility to choose, what we wanted to backup. <p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->Options to push backup to Oracle Cloud Infrastructure.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->Options to get problem statement/error in advance <span>&nbsp;</span>with features called <b>dryRun.</b><p></p></p> </td> \n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table> \n<h3>What is Disadvantage of using Instance Dump?</h3> \n<h1><p></p></h1> \n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"MsoTableGrid\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr> \n   <td valign=\"top\" width=\"471\"> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->It is Logical Backup. so challenges of mysqldump will still applies.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->While taking backup it does take LOCK on the schemas.<p></p></p> <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">\n     <!--[if !supportLists]--><span><span>·<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>\n     <!--[endif]-->Debugg is not an easy as files is divided into chunks.<p></p></p> </td> \n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table> \n<br>\n <div> \n  <div class=\"separator\">\n   <a
